Susan, a friend of mine, comes from Germany. One day, she asked me,excitedly: &lsquo;I heard that Germany in Chinese means a Land of Virtue. Is that true?&rsquo;
&lsquo;True.&rsquo; I said, &lsquo;DEGUO, Country of Virtue.&rsquo;
&lsquo;I love Chinese! Tell me more. What is France in Chinese?&rsquo;
&ndash; &lsquo;FAGUO, Legal Country.&rsquo;
&lsquo;Hm, it makes sense. How about America?&rsquo;
&ndash; &lsquo;MEIGUO, Beautiful Country.&rsquo;
&lsquo;Really? and Britain?&rsquo;
&ndash; &lsquo;YINGJILI, Lucky flowers.&rsquo;
&lsquo;Funny! and the Netherlands?
